news.title: Strike still on to revoke construction permit for Bhutani project in Sancoale
news.para: Opposition panch members from Sancoale village have demanded revocation of the project, alleging that the project proponent has failed to comply with 35 observations, NOCs and permissions in the technical clearance issued by the Mormugao Planning and Development Authority (MPDA).

news.title: Telangana government sanctions Rs 24,269 crore for Hyderabad metro phase-II
news.para: Five Metro corridors covering 76.4 km will be undertaken jointly by the state govt (Hyderabad Airport Metro Limited) and the Centre on a 50:50 basis.

news.title: Delhi: 18,000 MT construction & demolition waste removed by MCD to check dust
news.para: Mayor Shelly Oberoi stated, "We will continue to clear C&D waste from all over Delhi, and residents can report instances on the MCD311 app to get waste lifted from their surroundings."

news.title: Nagpur civic body auctions Orange City plot for Rs 91 crore
news.para: Plot number four, measuring 4,294.05 square metres, attracted bids from two prominent builders, with Praful Ved Infra emerging as the highest bidder at Rs91 crore, outpacing the second-highest offer of Rs82 crore.

news.title: Goa housing board tweaks its rules for homebuyers’ benefit
news.para: The allotment committee has been replaced by a scrutiny committee, which must complete the scrutiny process for all applications within 30 days.

news.title: Lower sales realisation hit margins of cement manufacturers in Q2 FY25
news.para: Industry observers said the increase in sales volume of UltraTech and Ambuja Cements is mainly due to the several acquisitions by both companies that consolidated their position further in the industry.

news.title: Sebi proposes to allow InvITs, REITs, SM REITs to use interest rate derivatives for hedging risk
news.para: ​Also, the regulator has suggested approving locked-in units for REITs and InvITs to be transferred among sponsors and their groups, similar to rules for promoters in listed companies, to help sponsors manage their holdings without compromising "skin in the game".

news.title: Chennai residents struggle to form apartment associations
news.para: The recently unveiled Tamil Nadu Apartment Ownership Rules stipulate that a minimum of four apartment owners must form an association, draft bylaws, and register it before pursuing redevelopment.

news.title: Ponda civic body to lease entire market complex after several failed auctions
news.para: Inaugurated in Dec 2011, the market complex has been underutilised, with only 29 of 154 shops occupied. Despite auctions, PMC has been unable to find takers for the remaining shops for over a decade.

news.title: Bombay HC orders state to vacate Dadar flat over 20 year rent dispute
news.para: The HC ended a 20-year-old eviction battle by directing the State and the Mumbai police commissioner, whose designation was on the rent receipts as the tenant, to hand over vacant possession of the flat by the end of Nov.

news.title: Tamil Nadu housing board fined for excess water charges and hidden charges
news.para: K Iyappan, a state secretariat employee, had rented a TNHB property in Chennai between Nov 2020 and Oct 2021. During his 13-month stay, he was charged 80 per month for water, despite an agreed rate of 50, and was additionally billed 5,300 in mobile water charges not listed in the original rental terms.

news.title: Goa: TCP department approves 1.2 lakh sq meter land conversion for development
news.para: Of the 1.2 lakh sqm approved for conversion, 57,225sqm of partly orchard land and no-development slope in Parcem, Pernem, is for Lilah Project Realty One LLP, a luxury real estate firm that has links with Isprava Luxury Realty One LLP

news.title: Federal Bank acquires 1.01 lakh sq ft space from Varde Partners in Mumbai for Rs 300 crore
news.para: Federal Bank has acquired over 1.01 lakh sq ft of office space for Rs 330 crore in Mumbai’s Wadala locality, covering the 12th to 16th floor of the VIOS Tower. This deal, including 145 car parking slots, reflects a strategic consolidation of its operations in Mumbai's financial hub.

news.title: DDA to offer 2,500 flats in phase two of Sasta Ghar scheme from November 14
news.para: Over 2,500 flats will be offered in Rohini, Dwarka, Mangolpuri, Ramgarh, Loknayakpuram, Siraspur, Narela, and other parts of the city under this scheme. The cost of the flats will start from Rs 11.5 lakh onwards, and will be sold on a first-come, first-served basis.

news.title: No hearing in revenue court once civil suit filed in land dispute cases: Madhya Pradesh HC
news.para: The petitioner in the case, Abhishek Nigam from Bhopal, said he and Amresh Shrivastava jointly purchased land in Jabalpur district. In 2011, they moved an application before the tehsildar for the division of property.

news.title: Hyderabad: Sai Surya Developers' owner arrested for defrauding buyers of Rs 50 crore
news.para: The accused, Kancharla Sathish Chandra Gupta, proprietor of Sai Surya Developers, was taken into custody following a complaint from a person, who paid a significant sum for a plot in a fabricated layout at Vattinagulapally village in Rangareddy district.

news.title: Property registrations in Mumbai rise 22% to 12,960 units in October 2024: Report
news.para: Citing Maharashtra government data, real estate consultant Knight Frank India said the Mumbai city (area under BMC jurisdiction) saw higher registration of properties during October this year on the back of two major festivals -- Dussehra and Diwali.

news.title: Around 80 newly constructed model houses remain unallotted in Hubballi
news.para: According to sources, the existing houses of the beneficiaries are very close to the Unkal-Hosur bypass road. As the city is growing fast, the traffic movement is slow on this road.

news.title: US judge approves $110 million settlements with Compass, Redfin in home sale commission case
news.para: A wave of lawsuits accused major U.S. brokers of violating antitrust law by requiring sellers to pay a commission to a buyer's agent in order to list their homes for sale.

news.title: House prices in Britain rise by 0.1% in October 2024: Nationwide
news.para: Compared with October last year prices were 2.4% higher, a weaker annual increase than September's 3.2% rise and below the median forecast for a 2.8% gain in the Reuters poll.
